</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upolaris66.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Polaris66</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/27/02 6:08:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22456.topic&index=84>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Oldest Most Annoying Bugs in EQ (Add Yours)</span><hr size=1> These aren't bugs per se, just oversights on the designers' part.  Someone caught part of it earlier re:no /time on the moon, but here's everything 'odd' I've noticed about Luclin:<br>
<br>
1) If Luclin zones can't be seen from Norrath, why can Norrath be seen from Luclin zones?<br>
<br>
2) The sun doesn't move, there is no day or night, but it gets lighter and darker?<br>
<br>
3) If there is a 'dark side of the moon' that can never be seen from Norrath that doesn't mean that no light shines there.  It just means that the moon rotates at the same speed that it orbits.<br>
<br>
4) And there would still be day and night, too.  Full moon from <br>
Norrath == full night in Luclin zones. New moon (no moon) from Norrath == full day in Luclin zones.  Assuming a similar orbital configuration to that of Earth and its moon, a full day (day+night cycle) would be roughly 28 days.<br>
<br>
5) Except that I've never seen anything but a full moon from Norrath, which implies that it does not orbit Norrath but is a fixed object in space.  Though that would explain most of the above, it poses its own problems (why doesn't it get sucked into orbit of Norrath or its sun?)<br>
<br>
I know, a fantasy game has no need for an accurate astronomical model, but c'mon people. Think a little. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugaav.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaav</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/27/02 8:57:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22456.topic&index=85>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bugs</span><hr size=1> That last post was one of the most amusing things I've read in a while.<br>
